Remarks

Provides convenient fluent syntax for creating ignored wrappers, typically used when constructing metadata records from Roslyn symbols.

GeneratorIgnored<T>(T)

Wraps a value so it won't affect incremental generator equality comparisons.

Declaration
public static GeneratorIgnored<T> GeneratorIgnored<T>(this T value)
Parameters
Type Name Description
T value

The value to wrap.
Returns
Type Description
GeneratorIgnored<T>

A wrapped value that appears equal to all other GeneratorIgnored<T> instances regardless of the wrapped value.
Type Parameters
Name Description
T

The type of value to wrap.
Examples
var location = symbol.Locations.First().GeneratorIgnored();
// location changes won't trigger regeneration
